  "local_port": 44332,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can one use Bootstrap?",
  "response": "Bootstrap is a popular front-end framework used for designing responsive and modern websites quickly and easily. Here's a step-by-step guide on how to use Bootstrap:\n\n### 1. Setup Bootstrap\n\n**Option 1: Using a CDN**\n\nThe easiest way to get started with Bootstrap is to include it via a CDN (Content Delivery Network):\n\n- Include Bootstrap CSS in the `<head>` section of your HTML:\n\n  ```html\n  <link href=\"https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/5.1.3/css/bootstrap.min.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n  ```\n\n- Include Bootstrap Bundle JS (which includes Popper) before the closing `</body>` tag:\n\n  ```html\n  <script src=\"https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/5.1.3/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js\"></script>\n  ```\n\n**Option 2: Download Bootstrap**\n\nYou can also download Bootstrap and include the files in your project. Go to the [Bootstrap website](https://getbootstrap.com/) and download the latest version. Then, include the CSS and JS files in your project:\n\n- Link the CSS file in the `<head>`:\n\n  ```html\n  <link href=\"path/to/bootstrap.min.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n  ```\n\n- Link the JS bundle before the closing `</body>` tag:\n\n  ```html\n  <script src=\"path/to/bootstrap.bundle.min.js\"></script>\n  ```\n\n**Option 3: Install via Package Manager**\n\nIf you're using a build tool, you can install Bootstrap via npm:\n\n```bash\nnpm install bootstrap\n```\n\nThen import Bootstrap in your JavaScript file:\n\n```javascript\nimport 'bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css';\nimport 'bootstrap/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js';\n```\n\n### 2. Understand the Grid System\n\nBootstrap uses a responsive 12-column grid system. Here\u2019s an example of how to use it:\n\n```html\n<div class=\"container\">\n  <div class=\"row\">\n    <div class=\"col-md-4\">Column 1</div>\n    <div class=\"col-md-4\">Column 2</div>\n    <div class=\"col-md-4\">Column 3</div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n```\n\n- `.container` or `.container-fluid` is used to wrap the contents.\n- `.row` is used to create a new row.\n- `.col` classes are used to define columns. You can use different classes for responsiveness like `col-sm-6`, `col-md-4`, etc.\n\n### 3. Use Components\n\nBootstrap comes with a variety of pre-styled components like buttons, navigation, alerts, modals, and much more. Here are a few examples:\n\n**Button**\n\n```html\n<button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">Primary Button</button>\n```\n\n**Navbar**\n\n```html\n<nav class=\"navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-light bg-light\">\n  <a class=\"navbar-brand\" href=\"#\">Navbar</a>\n  ...\n</nav>\n```\n\n**Alert**\n\n```html\n<div class=\"alert alert-warning\" role=\"alert\">\n  This is a warning alert\u2014check it out!\n</div>\n```\n\n### 4. Customize with CSS\n\nWhile Bootstrap provides a lot of built-in styles, you can still customize your website with additional CSS. Simply link your own CSS file after Bootstrap's CSS file:\n\n```html\n<link href=\"custom-styles.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n```\n\n### 5. Explore JavaScript Plugins\n\nBootstrap\u2019s JavaScript plugins can be used to add functionality like dropdowns, modals, tooltips, etc. Ensure you have included Bootstrap\u2019s JS bundle or include individual plugins as needed.\n\nFor example, to use a modal, you\u2019ll need HTML structure and Bootstrap's JS:\n\n```html\n<!-- Trigger -->\n<button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-primary\" data-bs-toggle=\"modal\" data-bs-target=\"#myModal\">\n  Launch demo modal\n</button>\n\n<!-- Modal -->\n<div class=\"modal fade\" id=\"myModal\" tabindex=\"-1\" aria-labelledby=\"exampleModalLabel\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n  <div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n    <div class=\"modal-content\">\n      <div class=\"modal-header\">\n        <h5 class=\"modal-title\" id=\"exampleModalLabel\">Modal title</h5>\n        <button type=\"button\" class=\"btn-close\" data-bs-dismiss=\"modal\" aria-label=\"Close\"></button>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"modal-body\">\n        ...\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"modal-footer\">\n        <button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-secondary\" data-bs-dismiss=\"modal\">Close</button>\n        <button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">Save changes</button>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n```\n\n### 6. Explore Documentation\n\nBootstrap\u2019s official documentation is a great resource to explore components, utilities, and customization options. You can find it at [getbootstrap.com](https://getbootstrap.com/).\n\nBy following these steps, you can effectively use Bootstrap to build responsive, mobile-first web applications efficiently.",
